WEBVTT

00:02.403 --> 00:05.004
             [♪♪♪]

00:56.824 --> 00:57.722
Congratulations, Tony.

00:57.757 --> 00:59.191
            Oh, thank you.

00:59.226 --> 01:00.625
            Hey, what for?

01:04.965 --> 01:06.865
Congratulations,
captain.

01:06.900 --> 01:09.034
            Yeah. What did I do?

01:16.810 --> 01:18.409
Well...

01:18.445 --> 01:20.245
there you are,
captain.

01:20.280 --> 01:21.679
Congratulations.

01:21.715 --> 01:22.881
           Thank you, sir.

01:22.916 --> 01:24.749
             What's everybody
          congratulating me for?

01:24.784 --> 01:26.417
You haven't
heard the news?

01:26.453 --> 01:28.386
       No, sir. I just got in
       from a mission to Canada.

01:28.421 --> 01:29.487
      I-- I don't know anything.

01:29.522 --> 01:32.290
    Then let me be the first
          to tell you.

01:32.326 --> 01:35.526
     You and Captain Healey
   are on the promotion list.

01:36.130 --> 01:37.095
             Major.

01:37.130 --> 01:38.930
            Well...

01:38.965 --> 01:39.964
           how about that.

01:40.000 --> 01:42.334
You'll be losing
your railroad tracks.

01:42.369 --> 01:43.835
              Ha! Well,

01:43.870 --> 01:44.936
        that's wonderful.

01:44.971 --> 01:46.305
                  I--

01:46.340 --> 01:47.706
             I-- I bet you
          Roger's happy, huh?

01:47.741 --> 01:49.575
How soon will you be ready
to take off again?

01:49.610 --> 01:51.376
   Oh, right away, sir. Why?

01:51.412 --> 01:54.012
        General Peterson
   wants you and Major Healey

01:54.047 --> 01:55.314
to fly to Nellis Air Force Base,

01:55.349 --> 01:57.549
      and then on to
  Stead Air Force Base.

01:57.584 --> 01:59.317
He wants you to do
a few lectures

01:59.352 --> 02:01.453
on, uh, winged
spacecraft, and, uh,

02:01.488 --> 02:03.422
at the advanced fighter
weapon school there.

02:03.457 --> 02:05.323
       Oh, good. Good.
       I'd love that.

02:05.359 --> 02:07.559
    Give me a chance to see
  some old buddies from Korea.

02:07.594 --> 02:08.726
     I'll tell the general.

02:08.762 --> 02:10.228
                Roger that.

02:10.264 --> 02:11.596
    Oh, um...

02:11.631 --> 02:12.864
      major?

02:15.102 --> 02:16.668
     Uh...

02:16.704 --> 02:17.736
  major.

02:17.771 --> 02:19.104
           Oh, uh...

02:19.139 --> 02:20.405
        I'm sorry, sir.

02:20.440 --> 02:22.641
    I have no desire to, uh,

02:22.676 --> 02:24.442
     break up certain, uh,

02:24.478 --> 02:26.812
     peculiar occurrences,

02:26.847 --> 02:29.414
      but there are things
    that a captain might do

02:29.449 --> 02:32.417
that a major
definitely would not do.

02:33.153 --> 02:34.720
    Do I make myself clear?

02:34.755 --> 02:36.654
           Yes, sir.

02:36.689 --> 02:38.356
       Good.

02:38.391 --> 02:41.259
Just so long as we
understand each other.

02:42.796 --> 02:44.830
Oh, thank you very much, doctor.

02:44.865 --> 02:46.197
          My pleasure.

02:46.233 --> 02:48.099
    Major.

02:55.809 --> 02:57.275
 Good morning,
    master.

02:57.311 --> 02:58.810
           Jeannie, what are you
                doing here?

02:58.845 --> 03:00.512
    I brought you
    this telegram.

03:00.547 --> 03:02.347
I thought it
might be important.

03:04.551 --> 03:05.650
                    Oh.

03:05.685 --> 03:07.486
                    [CHUCKLES]
                 How about that.
      [GIGGLES]

03:07.521 --> 03:09.887
       It's from one of the boys
             in Washington

03:09.923 --> 03:10.888
              congratulating me.

03:10.924 --> 03:12.324
              I've been promoted
                   to major.

03:12.359 --> 03:13.958
  Oh, how wonderful.

03:13.994 --> 03:15.059
      [GIGGLES]

03:15.095 --> 03:16.628
Oh, what does it mean?

03:16.663 --> 03:18.396
                  Maj--
        Oh, that means I've been

03:18.432 --> 03:20.132
                promoted to
          the next highest rank.

03:20.167 --> 03:22.700
Oh, yeah. One of these days I'm
 gonna be a lieutenant colonel,

03:22.736 --> 03:23.968
  and then, uh...

03:24.004 --> 03:25.637
Well, then I hope
to be a colonel.

03:25.672 --> 03:27.506
        What will happen
    when you are a colonel?

03:27.541 --> 03:29.741
    Well, then I get to wear
     birds on my shoulders.

03:30.777 --> 03:32.511
   And this is what you wish?

03:32.546 --> 03:34.812
          Uh, you bet.

03:45.059 --> 03:47.426
             [♪♪♪]

04:46.453 --> 04:48.587
Are you sure you would not
like to take me with you?

04:48.622 --> 04:51.089
     Well, Jeannie, if they ever
         found out about you,

04:51.124 --> 04:52.323
                they'd bust me
                 to civilian.

04:52.359 --> 04:53.592
[DOORBELL RINGS]

04:53.627 --> 04:54.826
           Oh, that'll be Roger.

05:00.967 --> 05:02.634
            Good morning, major.

05:02.669 --> 05:04.202
Good morning, major.

05:04.238 --> 05:06.104
                    I like
              the sound of that.
   So do I.

05:06.139 --> 05:07.805
             Hey, you all ready
           for Nellie and Stead?

05:07.841 --> 05:08.840
    Yup.

05:08.875 --> 05:10.141
          And who is
           Nellie?

05:10.176 --> 05:12.410
Oh. Nellie's the nickname
for Nellis Air Force Base.

05:12.446 --> 05:13.778
                  Hi, Jeannie.

05:13.813 --> 05:15.880
Good morning,
Major Healey.

05:15.915 --> 05:17.749
           Boy, the three of us
          are gonna have a ball.

05:17.784 --> 05:19.016
     The three of us?

05:19.052 --> 05:20.685
No, the two of us.
Jeannie's not going.

05:20.720 --> 05:22.186
                 What did you--
               what did you say?

05:22.221 --> 05:24.188
  I said Jeannie's not going.

05:24.223 --> 05:25.890
                 You're kidding.

05:25.926 --> 05:28.092
        General Peterson said
    when we finished our lecture

05:28.127 --> 05:29.694
              we could have
        a few days leave, right?

05:29.730 --> 05:30.695
          Yeah.

05:30.731 --> 05:31.696
         Since Stead is only a--

05:31.732 --> 05:33.097
          Only a couple of miles
                from Reno,

05:33.133 --> 05:34.499
               you said we could
                hop over there.

05:34.535 --> 05:36.000
      Yeah, that's right.

05:36.036 --> 05:37.536
            And you're seriously
                  thinking

05:37.571 --> 05:39.070
                of going to Reno
                without Jeannie?

05:39.105 --> 05:40.772
          Oh, no, no.
  I-I'm not thinking about it.

05:40.808 --> 05:43.308
 I've already made up my mind.
       Jeannie can't go.

05:44.611 --> 05:45.677
                     W--

05:46.780 --> 05:48.246
                    I will not
                  be in the way.

05:48.281 --> 05:49.548
See? She will not
be in the way.

05:49.583 --> 05:50.682
You can't
leave her here.

05:50.717 --> 05:52.584
Listen, 10 minutes
with her in the casino,

05:52.619 --> 05:54.385
and you'll come back
a multimillionaire.

05:54.421 --> 05:56.054
       I don't want to be
      a multimillionaire.

05:56.089 --> 05:57.856
Well, how about
a plain millionaire?

05:57.891 --> 05:59.724
             Roger, if I wanted
            to be a millionaire,

05:59.759 --> 06:01.326
              I wouldn't have
           joined the Air Force.

06:01.361 --> 06:02.527
Become a millionaire for me.

06:02.562 --> 06:04.529
I always wanted to have
a millionaire friend.

06:04.564 --> 06:05.964
             You're just wasting
                  your time.

06:05.999 --> 06:07.232
                   You and I
              are going to Reno.

06:07.267 --> 06:09.000
                   Jeannie is
                  staying here.

06:09.036 --> 06:10.501
          ROGER:
Will you tell me something?

06:10.537 --> 06:14.038
How did you ever pass
the Air Force intelligence test?

06:14.073 --> 06:15.340
Jeannie, in.

06:15.375 --> 06:17.008
    I have never seen Reno.

06:17.043 --> 06:18.876
In.

06:18.912 --> 06:21.045
   Are you sure you would not
   like to be a millionaire?

06:21.080 --> 06:22.547
                          [TAPS
                        ON LAMP]

06:24.117 --> 06:25.783
      Have a nice journey.

06:27.988 --> 06:29.621
              Thank you.

06:29.656 --> 06:32.156
           I better go get
    my flight bag. Take it easy.

06:32.191 --> 06:34.325
Well, if you don't want
to become a millionaire,

06:34.360 --> 06:35.359
I can't force you to.

06:35.395 --> 06:37.328
It's your genie.

06:40.667 --> 06:43.601
              On the other hand,
                I'm your buddy.

06:43.637 --> 06:45.570
        And if you should become
            a millionaire...

06:45.605 --> 06:48.139
             how mad at me
             could you get?

06:50.644 --> 06:51.609
             Jeannie.

06:51.645 --> 06:54.311
             Jeannie, can I
              talk to you?

06:55.515 --> 06:57.481
Yes, Major Healey.
                     Sh!

06:57.517 --> 06:58.950
                 Would you--?
             Would you really--?

06:58.985 --> 07:00.451
              Would you really
             like to go with us?

07:00.486 --> 07:01.920
Oh, I would like to!

07:01.955 --> 07:04.989
                   Ah...
              Ha-ha-ha-ha-ha.

07:07.093 --> 07:08.927
   Ooh.
              Welcome to Reno.

07:08.962 --> 07:10.962
 [LAUGHS]

07:13.934 --> 07:15.066
                    Ahem.

07:17.470 --> 07:18.436
              [SIGHS]

07:18.471 --> 07:19.571
              Ahem.

07:20.607 --> 07:21.873
                Roge. Uh...look,
                   believe me,

07:21.908 --> 07:23.875
I'm doing
the right thing.

07:23.910 --> 07:25.443
Jeannie, I'll be back
in a few days.

07:25.478 --> 07:27.178
I'll let you out then.

07:27.213 --> 07:29.681
 Oh, don't look
    so glum.

07:29.716 --> 07:31.282
You'll feel better
once we get there.

07:31.317 --> 07:33.317
     I feel better already.

07:36.322 --> 07:39.290
             [♪♪♪]

08:17.764 --> 08:18.930
             Uh, easy with that.

08:18.965 --> 08:20.164
           [CHUCKLES]

08:20.199 --> 08:21.933
 I've got a few important
     things in there.

08:21.968 --> 08:23.200
                Nice place, huh?

08:23.236 --> 08:24.736
Yeah, yeah. Nice.

08:24.771 --> 08:26.203
I've got the feeling
these will be

08:26.239 --> 08:27.839
two of the luckiest
days of our lives.

08:27.874 --> 08:29.306
                Oh, yeah? What
             makes you think so?

08:29.342 --> 08:30.742
Oh, just one
of my crazy hunches.

08:30.777 --> 08:32.876
Uh, look, why don't you
go down to the casino?

08:32.912 --> 08:34.145
Uh, I'll be right there.

08:34.179 --> 08:35.847
         Hm? No. I'm in no rush.
            I'll wait for you.

08:35.881 --> 08:37.849
     Ah. Well,
    I tell you,

08:37.884 --> 08:40.684
I have to call a friend,
and it's kind of personal.

08:40.720 --> 08:43.453
        Oh, I see. I didn't know
       you had a friend in Reno.

08:43.489 --> 08:45.123
Well, uh,
she just got here.

08:45.158 --> 08:46.257
   [LAUGHS]

08:46.292 --> 08:47.458
                 I'll see you
                 downstairs.

08:47.493 --> 08:48.492
Yeah. Uh, look, uh...

08:48.528 --> 08:50.828
 Here's, uh--
 Here's $50.

08:50.864 --> 08:51.829
     Uh...

08:51.865 --> 08:53.397
just bet it
for me, huh?

08:53.432 --> 08:55.800
        Oh, wait a minute.
 You want me to bet $50 for you?

08:55.835 --> 08:57.601
That's right. Bet it
on anything you like.

08:57.637 --> 08:59.603
       No, Roger. I won't accept
          the responsibility.

08:59.639 --> 09:02.606
Oh, well, be my guest
and bet it all at once.

09:02.642 --> 09:04.642
Let's be
big about it, huh?

09:04.678 --> 09:06.210
               You sure you know
              what you're doing?

09:06.245 --> 09:07.945
  You bet.

09:07.981 --> 09:09.947
          Okay, if you're sure.
        I'll see you downstairs.

09:09.983 --> 09:11.482
Downstairs.
Downstairs.

09:11.517 --> 09:14.152
Oh, I've got a feeling that $50

09:14.187 --> 09:17.155
        is going to turn
    into a little gold mine.

09:17.190 --> 09:19.957
Jeannie...you can come out now.

09:23.196 --> 09:24.428
            Jeannie!

09:24.463 --> 09:25.596
             C--

09:27.701 --> 09:31.602
        Oh. I must have
      lost her at Nellie.

09:31.637 --> 09:33.571
            My $50.

09:40.480 --> 09:41.846
             Wheee!

09:41.882 --> 09:43.447
           [LAUGHS]

09:45.919 --> 09:48.185
             [PEOPLE CHATTERING,
              CHIPS CLATTERING]

09:50.524 --> 09:51.589
                        DEALER:
                      Coming up.

09:51.625 --> 09:53.558
                       DEALER 2:
                      And seven,
                      the loser.

09:53.593 --> 09:57.261
    All right, we have a new man
     coming up real quick-like.

09:57.296 --> 09:58.396
                  Here you go.

09:58.431 --> 09:59.564
              I beg
           your pardon?

09:59.599 --> 10:00.632
                     Make room
                  for the major.

10:00.667 --> 10:02.066
           We have a new shooter
                 coming up.

10:02.101 --> 10:04.368
             Get your bets down.
                All bets down.

10:04.404 --> 10:05.403
 I'd like to
  bet $50.

10:05.438 --> 10:07.104
         Fifty dollars.
      Here you are, major.

10:07.139 --> 10:08.339
                 Place your bet.

10:08.375 --> 10:10.708
                   All right,
               we're coming out.

10:10.744 --> 10:12.377
My money. What did you do
with my money?

10:12.412 --> 10:13.878
                  I just put
              on the line, Roge.

10:13.913 --> 10:16.748
All of it? You bet
the whole $50 on one roll?

10:16.783 --> 10:18.616
        Well, I-- I only did
        what you told me to.

10:18.651 --> 10:21.219
And you listened to me? What do
you think, money grows on trees?

10:21.254 --> 10:22.320
   I work hard
  for my money.

10:23.356 --> 10:26.123
             Snake eyes.
           The line loses.

10:27.426 --> 10:29.293
        You lost my $50.

10:29.328 --> 10:30.995
           Sorry, Roge.

10:31.031 --> 10:32.330
       It was your idea.

10:32.365 --> 10:34.232
      Why didn't you just
     throw it down a sewer?

10:34.267 --> 10:35.733
Do me a favor,
while you're here,

10:35.768 --> 10:36.968
will you keep away
from me?

10:37.003 --> 10:39.270
        You're bad luck.
            $50. Oh.

10:39.306 --> 10:40.572
             Roge, wait.

10:40.607 --> 10:42.373
                Are you betting,
                     major?

10:43.577 --> 10:44.875
 Oh, no. No.

10:44.911 --> 10:47.711
           All right, here comes
           another lucky roller.

10:49.115 --> 10:50.114
                   [SLOT MACHINE
                       SPINS]

10:50.150 --> 10:51.416
                         MAN:
                      All right.

10:51.451 --> 10:53.751
DEALER 2:
We have a new lucky
roller coming up.

10:53.786 --> 10:56.754
Who's the next roller?
Here we go.

10:56.789 --> 10:59.623
And seven,
the loser.

10:59.659 --> 11:01.725
DEALER:
Coming up.

11:02.996 --> 11:04.061
In.

11:05.498 --> 11:07.799
DEALER 2:
All right. We have
a new shooter coming up.

11:07.834 --> 11:09.768
Get your bets down...

11:13.372 --> 11:15.606
           Hey. I hit
           a jackpot.

11:15.641 --> 11:17.875
              Congratulations,
                   major.

11:17.911 --> 11:20.011
  Thank you. I've never played
      one of these before.

11:22.849 --> 11:24.782
       Oh. Put another dollar in
          to clear the jackpot

11:24.818 --> 11:26.150
                off the machine.

11:26.186 --> 11:27.718
              Oh.

11:32.993 --> 11:34.225
                   [SLOT MACHINE
                       RINGS]

11:34.261 --> 11:35.626
              Hey!

11:35.662 --> 11:37.929
                  I'd better get
                 another bucket.

11:45.972 --> 11:47.071
DEALER:
Coming up.

11:47.106 --> 11:48.573
                  [COINS CLANG]
                Oh! Another one!

11:48.608 --> 11:50.175
           I never had
        anything like this

11:50.210 --> 11:51.176
          happen to me
          in my life!

11:51.211 --> 11:52.644
               Oh, Jeannie!

11:52.679 --> 11:54.579
Oh. Shh.

11:54.614 --> 11:55.846
            Money, money, money.

11:55.882 --> 11:57.615
 Money, money, money.
  Oh, you did it.

11:57.651 --> 11:58.816
                Oh, hi, Roge.

11:58.851 --> 12:00.518
             All right, miss.
          I think that's enough.

12:00.554 --> 12:01.686
 You're not gonna
    quit now!

12:01.721 --> 12:03.188
                 Yeah, I'm gonna
                    quit now.

12:03.223 --> 12:05.590
   I'll have one of the boys
help you and bring your receipt.

12:05.625 --> 12:07.058
               Oh, thank you.
            And this is for you.

12:07.093 --> 12:08.326
      Yeah.

12:08.361 --> 12:10.195
Let's get back
to the crap table, huh?

12:10.230 --> 12:12.163
        It's such a nice day.
     I think I'll go for a swim.

12:12.199 --> 12:13.764
Oh, you can't afford
to go swimming!

12:13.800 --> 12:16.133
Come with me, and I'll buy you
your own swimming pool.

12:16.169 --> 12:17.435
                 Are you feeling
                    all right?

12:17.470 --> 12:19.537
I never felt better
in my life!

12:19.573 --> 12:21.806
    Now, wait a minute. I really
      don't feel like gambling.

12:21.841 --> 12:23.541
  Well, do it for me.

12:23.577 --> 12:25.042
              I thought you said
                I was bad luck.

12:25.078 --> 12:26.311
    Did I say that?
        Ha-ha!

12:26.346 --> 12:27.645
Oh, you're my rabbit's foot.

12:27.681 --> 12:29.347
I wouldn't make a move
without you.

12:29.382 --> 12:30.582
DEALER 2:
Place your bets.

12:30.617 --> 12:32.350
We have another
lucky shooter coming up!

12:32.385 --> 12:33.951
Are you betting,
major?

12:33.986 --> 12:35.319
                  No, no--
      Oh, of course he is.

12:35.354 --> 12:36.921
Here's $50.
Play it right on the line.

12:36.956 --> 12:38.222
                  Fifty dollars?
                  Wait a minute.

12:38.257 --> 12:39.824
           The last time we went
               through this--

12:39.859 --> 12:41.225
You're right.
It's not enough.

12:41.260 --> 12:42.793
Make it 100
on the line.

12:42.828 --> 12:44.062
                     A hundred
                      dollars?

12:44.097 --> 12:45.429
Don't keep
the man waiting.

12:48.768 --> 12:50.835
We're coming out
for a point.

12:50.870 --> 12:52.269
                   All right.

12:52.305 --> 12:53.771
            Uh-huh.

12:54.874 --> 12:58.076
           DEALER 2:
  Snake eyes. The line loses.

13:00.479 --> 13:01.979
                I'm sorry, uh,
                Roge. I'm sorry.

13:02.015 --> 13:03.547
Don't talk to me,
you Jonah.

13:04.851 --> 13:07.651
DEALER 2:
All right, who's
the next lucky roller?

13:07.687 --> 13:09.787
We're coming out
for another point. Here we go.

13:16.462 --> 13:18.495
Roger, I'm very sorry
I lost all that money.

13:18.531 --> 13:19.830
                 Oh, forget it.

13:19.865 --> 13:21.399
What's $150 of my money to you?

13:21.434 --> 13:23.300
      Oh, you're the last
      of the big spenders.

13:23.335 --> 13:26.103
      Now, wait a minute.
I didn't want to bet your money.

13:26.138 --> 13:27.304
    I-- You forced it on me.

13:27.339 --> 13:28.739
 Don't you know how to say no?

13:28.775 --> 13:30.641
 Look, do me a favor, will you?
         Go for a swim.

13:30.677 --> 13:32.043
           All right.
     And you do me a favor.

13:32.078 --> 13:33.678
   Don't ask me to bet
   your money for you.

13:33.713 --> 13:35.412
                  Don't worry,
                    I won't.

13:37.349 --> 13:38.783
Ha-ha. Would you
like something?

13:38.818 --> 13:40.084
                  Yeah. I'd like
                  another genie.

13:40.119 --> 13:41.285
                  Why didn't you
                     tell me

13:41.320 --> 13:42.987
             that your powers
          wouldn't work on dice?

13:43.022 --> 13:44.021
          But it does.

13:44.056 --> 13:45.222
        Are you kidding?

13:45.258 --> 13:46.591
 Those dice came up snake eyes.

13:46.626 --> 13:48.926
 I know. Did it not please you?

13:48.961 --> 13:51.128
           Please me?
  You know, you cost me 100--

13:51.164 --> 13:52.430
         Wait a minute.

13:52.465 --> 13:55.266
  You mean, you tried to roll
     those dice snake eyes?

13:55.302 --> 13:56.967
        Well, of course.

13:57.003 --> 13:58.102
          Oh, Jeannie.

13:58.137 --> 13:59.437
       Can you make them
          roll seven?

13:59.472 --> 14:00.505
        Yes.

14:00.540 --> 14:01.939
       Oh. And 11?

14:01.974 --> 14:03.007
              Yes.

14:03.042 --> 14:04.742
  Oh, Jeannie. Don't go away.

14:04.778 --> 14:06.510
      I'll be right back.

14:11.985 --> 14:13.384
              Oh, there you are,
                    buddy.

14:13.419 --> 14:14.886
               I've been looking
               all over for you.

14:14.921 --> 14:16.353
The name is Jonah,
remember?

14:16.389 --> 14:18.256
            Jonah. Oh, you're my
              good luck charm.

14:18.291 --> 14:19.791
              Look, here's $100.

14:19.826 --> 14:21.492
              I'd like you to go
              and bet it for me.

14:21.527 --> 14:22.726
    Forget it.

14:22.762 --> 14:23.895
                 Wait, where are
                    you going?

14:23.930 --> 14:25.029
 I'm going swimming.

14:25.064 --> 14:27.198
                Swimming? It's
             freezing out there.

14:27.233 --> 14:29.533
What are you talking about?
It must be, uh, 90 degrees.

14:29.568 --> 14:32.003
                Oh, at least
                  100, 110.

14:32.038 --> 14:33.604
         Look, I'm not gonna let
             a buddy of mine

14:33.639 --> 14:35.739
           go down there and get
           sunstroke. No, siree.

14:35.775 --> 14:37.842
   You get dressed, and we'll go
        down to the casino.

14:37.877 --> 14:39.210
 Ah. No, thank you.

14:39.245 --> 14:41.345
The "last of the big spenders"
is going swimming.

14:41.380 --> 14:43.214
                  Can't you
                 take a joke?

14:43.249 --> 14:45.016
Well, I don't know.
I haven't heard it yet.

14:45.051 --> 14:47.118
          Look, you think losing
             a couple dollars

14:47.153 --> 14:48.286
                means anything
                    to me?

14:48.321 --> 14:50.021
                    I was only
                 putting you on.

14:50.056 --> 14:51.956
          Wh-- Why don't we go
        down to the casino, huh?

14:51.991 --> 14:53.490
 Well, I got
 a better idea.
                      What?

14:53.526 --> 14:55.893
Why don't you
put on your trunks,
and we'll go swimming.

14:55.929 --> 14:57.962
I met a couple of nice,
young ladies downstairs,

14:57.997 --> 14:59.864
very attractive
and willing to have dinner.

14:59.899 --> 15:02.333
        Girls? Is that all
  you can think about, is girls?

15:02.368 --> 15:04.001
Well, look who's talking.

15:04.037 --> 15:06.270
You got the fattest little
black book I've ever seen.

15:06.306 --> 15:08.672
  That was the old Roger Healey.
     We can get girls anytime.

15:08.708 --> 15:10.241
              Boy, but how often
             do we come to Reno?

15:10.276 --> 15:11.575
    Too often.

15:11.611 --> 15:12.977
                Yeah. Yeah, I--

15:13.013 --> 15:13.978
                      Heh.

15:14.014 --> 15:15.679
             You're right. I'm--

15:15.715 --> 15:16.947
           I'm sorry.

15:16.983 --> 15:18.983
Oh, look, why don't--
Why don't you go have a--

15:19.019 --> 15:21.285
Have a good time, uh--

15:21.321 --> 15:23.087
    Don't worry
    about me. I--

15:24.357 --> 15:25.623
                    Roger.

15:25.658 --> 15:27.525
             Roger, is something
                troubling you?

15:27.560 --> 15:29.027
No, no. I'm--
I'm fine, I'm fine.

15:29.062 --> 15:30.028
  You, uh--

15:30.063 --> 15:31.195
You run along
and have fun.

15:31.231 --> 15:32.497
             Now, how am I gonna
                 have any fun

15:32.532 --> 15:33.964
              when you're acting
                  like this?

15:34.000 --> 15:36.600
Oh. I knew I could count on you.
We've been buddies a long time.

15:36.636 --> 15:38.102
We've been through
a lot together.

15:38.138 --> 15:39.237
                     Yeah.
               Most of it today.

15:39.272 --> 15:40.571
     Look,

15:40.606 --> 15:42.873
  I don't ask too many favors
        of you, but, uh,

15:42.909 --> 15:45.076
       I'm gonna ask you
       for one right now.

15:45.111 --> 15:46.077
          What is it?

15:46.112 --> 15:47.711
       Don't go swimming.

15:47.747 --> 15:49.914
   Uh, w-what kind of a favor
            is that?

15:49.949 --> 15:51.315
            [SIGHS]

15:51.351 --> 15:53.617
       Well, if I go down
   to that casino by myself,

15:53.653 --> 15:54.752
              I--

15:54.787 --> 15:55.986
 I'm liable to get in trouble.

15:57.790 --> 16:01.125
       I never...told you
    this before, but, uh...

16:01.160 --> 16:04.362
   I'm a compulsive gambler.

16:04.397 --> 16:07.030
     Roge, I never knew that
            about you.

16:07.066 --> 16:10.568
          I had my own
     floating crap game...

16:12.305 --> 16:13.704
   ...when I was 6 years old.

16:15.741 --> 16:17.341
            Tony...

16:18.844 --> 16:22.613
   would--? Would you go down
      and bet this for me?

16:22.648 --> 16:24.815
       You sure you know
      what you're saying?

16:24.850 --> 16:27.318
   You want me to bet this--?
        This $100 worth?

16:27.353 --> 16:28.319
         That's right.

16:28.354 --> 16:29.487
    And if I should lose it?

16:29.522 --> 16:30.988
          I'll laugh.

16:31.023 --> 16:33.724
        Roge, do me a favor.

16:33.760 --> 16:35.593
        When we get back
       to Cape Kennedy...

16:35.628 --> 16:38.129
 I want you to have a long talk
       with Dr. Bellows.

16:38.164 --> 16:39.363
Anything you say.

16:39.399 --> 16:40.431
Look, you get dressed.

16:40.466 --> 16:42.300
I'll meet you down
at the casino, huh?

16:47.907 --> 16:50.141
                Thank you, sir.

16:50.176 --> 16:52.510
           Oh, see what
           he gave me.

16:52.545 --> 16:53.877
Never mind that.

16:53.913 --> 16:56.114
Look, now remember
what I told you, okay?
                         Mm-hm.

16:56.149 --> 16:58.549
Oh. Here he comes.
You better keep out of sight.

16:58.585 --> 17:00.451
If he finds you here,
he'll kill both of us.

17:04.823 --> 17:07.558
Oh. Oh, there you are.
Oh, I knew I could count on you.

17:07.593 --> 17:09.026
                    I almost
                changed my mind.

17:09.060 --> 17:10.694
           I still think this is
             a mistake, Roger.

17:10.729 --> 17:12.762
Now look, don't worry about
a thing. Here's $50.

17:12.798 --> 17:14.498
  Bet it on anything you like.

17:14.532 --> 17:16.967
  Are you sure you're feeling
  all right? This is your $50.

17:17.002 --> 17:18.336
I can bet it on anything I like?

17:18.371 --> 17:19.637
   That's what I said, buddy.

17:19.672 --> 17:21.172
  And if I lose, you'll, uh--

17:21.207 --> 17:22.940
     I'll laugh. Ha-ha-ha!

17:22.976 --> 17:24.375
                    All right.

17:28.348 --> 17:30.747
                   Just sit
              right here, lucky.

17:30.783 --> 17:32.683
   Fifty dollars,
   please.
                          Fifty?

17:32.718 --> 17:35.086
               Ah, you heard
                 the man.

17:35.121 --> 17:36.720
               Here we go
               this time.

17:37.723 --> 17:38.856
               [WHISTLES]

17:41.094 --> 17:43.194
                      Blackjack.
                     House wins.

17:45.431 --> 17:46.763
                   You know what
                   you just did?

17:46.799 --> 17:50.001
                   You just lost
                      my $50.

17:50.036 --> 17:51.735
                     [LAUGHS
                  UNCOMFORTABLY]

17:51.770 --> 17:52.903
                Stay right here.

17:52.938 --> 17:54.472
             Uh, I've got to see
              a friend of mine.

17:54.507 --> 17:56.273
Yeah. Wait
a minute. Roger!

17:56.309 --> 17:58.842
                          Major.
          Yeah?

17:58.878 --> 18:00.144
                     Are you in,
                        major?

18:00.179 --> 18:01.512
    No. No, thanks.
    I don't gamble.

18:01.547 --> 18:04.515
                  Oh. Thank you,
                       sir.

18:06.752 --> 18:08.685
          Oh. Would you
          like a drink?

18:08.721 --> 18:10.821
              I can't afford it.
             You're breaking me.

18:10.856 --> 18:12.823
 Are you working for your master
        or for the house?

18:12.858 --> 18:14.225
Did it not go well?

18:14.260 --> 18:15.826
               That's right,
            it did not go well.

18:15.861 --> 18:17.395
        Oh, I am sorry.

18:17.430 --> 18:19.730
But I do not understand
this strange game

18:19.765 --> 18:21.232
that my master is playing.

18:21.267 --> 18:23.034
                 Well, you don't
                   understand--

18:23.069 --> 18:25.536
                  Oh. How stupid
                    can I get!

18:25.571 --> 18:28.372
Perhaps my master is right.
I-I think I will go home now.

18:28.408 --> 18:29.773
                  Oh, you can't
                  go home now.

18:29.808 --> 18:31.275
              We're in the verge
                of being rich.

18:31.310 --> 18:33.544
       You stay right here.
 I'll get him to the crap table.

18:33.579 --> 18:35.446
            Remember, seven, 11.
                   Got it?

18:35.481 --> 18:36.747
    I got it.

18:36.782 --> 18:38.982
        Oh, I've been waiting
    for this moment all my life.

18:39.018 --> 18:40.117
                       Oh.

18:41.220 --> 18:42.386
DEALER:
Coming up.

18:46.158 --> 18:48.091
               Take him
            into my office.

18:57.002 --> 18:59.236
                  Now...what was
                 that all about?

18:59.271 --> 19:01.772
We caught him trying to
cheat at the crap table.

19:01.808 --> 19:02.773
                      Oh. Oh.

19:02.809 --> 19:04.508
             Do, uh, many people
                  try that?

19:04.544 --> 19:06.343
Only once, major.

19:07.580 --> 19:09.713
                    Oh, I see.
                      I see.

19:09.749 --> 19:11.415
                What will happen
                     to him?

19:11.451 --> 19:12.917
Oh, let us
just say that

19:12.952 --> 19:15.118
the guards will
take care of him.

19:15.154 --> 19:16.520
                Yeah. Let's just
                    say that.

19:16.556 --> 19:18.656
Are you having any luck
at the tables?

19:18.691 --> 19:20.023
                 No. No, no, no.
                     No, no.

19:20.059 --> 19:22.025
     I'm just placing a few bets
        for a friend of mine.

19:22.061 --> 19:23.126
                  I'm not much
                  of a gambler.

19:23.162 --> 19:25.028
Well, enjoy yourself.

19:25.064 --> 19:27.631
I've got to go
take care of someone.

19:29.569 --> 19:30.801
     Oh.
                    [GASPS]

19:30.837 --> 19:32.770
I thought I lost you.
Don't scare me like that.

19:32.805 --> 19:33.904
                 Yeah, where are
                    we going?

19:33.940 --> 19:35.372
To the crap table.

19:35.407 --> 19:37.741
     No, no. You really are a
 compulsive gambler, aren't you?

19:37.777 --> 19:39.743
You know how it is.
Easy come, easy go. Ha.

19:41.514 --> 19:44.649
           And seven,
        the line loses.

19:44.684 --> 19:46.684
     ROGER:
Ah. Here we are.

19:46.719 --> 19:48.319
   Excuse me.

19:48.354 --> 19:50.621
 Well, uh, let's shoot
   the works, huh?

19:50.657 --> 19:51.955
        Ah.

19:51.991 --> 19:53.257
                What's
             the matter?

19:53.293 --> 19:54.525
   All I've got
   is a dollar.

19:54.560 --> 19:56.026
Look, Tony,
do me a favor, will you?

19:56.061 --> 19:58.028
Will you lend me $1000?
I'll give it right back.

19:58.063 --> 19:59.763
       A thousand dollars?

19:59.799 --> 20:01.532
     Five hundred?
              No.

20:01.567 --> 20:03.334
          Two-fifty.
            Stop it, Roge.

20:03.369 --> 20:06.136
        A hundred.
     Haven't you gambled enough?

20:06.171 --> 20:07.338
Fifty.

20:07.373 --> 20:08.673
        I'll bet you a dollar.

20:08.708 --> 20:09.940
                      We have
                  a new shooter.

20:09.975 --> 20:11.575
                 He's coming out
                   for a point.

20:16.415 --> 20:19.150
               Seven! The winner
                 pay the line.

20:19.185 --> 20:21.218
     Oh.
            Here's your
       two dollars. Let's go.

20:21.253 --> 20:23.988
Oh. You can't go. Leave it--
Leave it on the line.

20:24.023 --> 20:26.490
           All right, coming out
             for a point again.

20:29.929 --> 20:33.130
              Eleven! The winner
                 pay the line.

20:33.166 --> 20:34.231
      Okay, that's enough.

20:34.266 --> 20:36.934
Oh, leave it.
Leave it. Leave it.

20:36.969 --> 20:39.436
           All right. Coming out
            for another number.

20:39.471 --> 20:41.371
                  Here we go.

20:46.045 --> 20:49.112
              Number seven.
        The winner pay the line.

20:49.148 --> 20:50.848
Oh! Oh! I knew
this was my lucky day.

20:50.883 --> 20:52.550
Oh. Just leave it
all on the line.

20:52.585 --> 20:55.353
  Oh, hey, Tony. Why don't you
  put some of your money down?

20:55.388 --> 20:56.821
 Because I don't like to gamble.

20:56.856 --> 20:58.556
         I'm only doing this
         as a favor to you.

20:58.591 --> 21:00.023
     Oh. And what a favor.

21:00.059 --> 21:01.592
I'll never
forget you for this.

21:01.627 --> 21:04.161
         All right. We're coming
         out for another number.

21:05.731 --> 21:08.632
        Number seven! The winner
              pay the line.

21:08.667 --> 21:09.633
    Oh! Oh!

21:09.668 --> 21:11.502
               We're hot.
Oh. Oh, boy!

21:11.537 --> 21:13.103
  Oh, look at
 all the chips.

21:13.139 --> 21:14.804
Look at all
these chips. Oh.

21:14.840 --> 21:16.507
    Leave them all.
    Leave them all.

21:16.542 --> 21:18.642
                   All right,
                here we go again

21:18.677 --> 21:20.810
                    for another
                   lucky number.

21:20.846 --> 21:22.712
                  Roll the dice.

21:24.717 --> 21:26.784
         Did you just see
        what those dice did?

21:26.819 --> 21:27.785
          Did you see?

21:27.820 --> 21:30.487
               Seven. The winner
                 pay the line.

21:30.522 --> 21:31.722
   Oh, money, money,
        money.

21:31.757 --> 21:32.723
               Roger, calm down.

21:32.758 --> 21:33.724
    Oh. Calm down?

21:33.759 --> 21:34.992
         Roger, you got
         a lot of money.

21:35.027 --> 21:36.594
       Why don't you pull
        some of it back?

21:36.629 --> 21:37.795
       ROGER:
Oh, are you kidding?

21:37.830 --> 21:39.430
Bet-a-Million Healey,
they call me.

21:39.465 --> 21:40.531
Oh. Put it all
on the line.

21:40.566 --> 21:41.998
     I hope you know
    what you're doing.

21:42.034 --> 21:43.099
   This can't go on
       forever.

21:43.135 --> 21:45.135
Who said so?

21:45.170 --> 21:46.903
     All right, we're coming out
            for a point.

21:51.444 --> 21:54.211
         Seven. The winner
           pay the line.

21:54.247 --> 21:55.479
                      What's
                  going on here?

21:55.514 --> 21:56.913
      They're our dice.

21:56.949 --> 21:58.449
                      Give him
                   another pair.

21:58.484 --> 21:59.816
         All right, folks.

21:59.852 --> 22:01.652
             Here comes
        the next lucky roll.

22:01.687 --> 22:04.287
             Here you go.
      We're looking for a point.

22:07.860 --> 22:10.761
                   DEALER 2:
               Seven. The winner
                 pay the line.

22:10.796 --> 22:11.762
             TONY:
         You see that?

22:11.798 --> 22:13.296
     Did you see that? Huh?

22:13.332 --> 22:14.898
ROGER:
Oh! Keep rolling!

22:14.934 --> 22:16.366
You've got
the golden touch! Oh!

22:16.401 --> 22:18.936
    Roger, take it easy. You're
 making a spectacle of yourself.

22:18.971 --> 22:21.138
  Millionaires don't make
 spectacles of themselves.

22:21.173 --> 22:22.439
       They're eccentric!

22:22.474 --> 22:24.641
DEALER 2:
All right, we're coming
out for a point.

22:24.677 --> 22:26.009
                     Here we go.

22:26.044 --> 22:27.277
              Calm down.
Settle down.

22:27.312 --> 22:28.478
                    Right out
                for a point now.

22:31.584 --> 22:33.283
               Seven. The winner
                 pay the line!

22:33.319 --> 22:35.085
Oh! Oh, we're winning!
We're all winning!

22:35.121 --> 22:36.553
           Thank you.
      Thank you very much.

22:36.589 --> 22:37.687
     Just a minute.

22:37.723 --> 22:39.223
          Now, wait a minute.
             Wait a minute!

22:39.258 --> 22:40.257
     Just a minute.

22:40.292 --> 22:42.025
               Oh, sorry,
             Mr. Phillips.

22:50.135 --> 22:51.335
     What's the matter
         with you?

22:51.370 --> 22:53.003
     Are you a sore loser
        or something?

22:53.038 --> 22:55.372
I thought you didn't
like gambling, major.

22:55.408 --> 22:57.574
            I don't. I'm just
         doing it for my friend.

22:57.610 --> 22:59.176
             ROGER:
  Yeah. A millionaire friend.

22:59.211 --> 23:01.311
 Something wrong with the dice?

23:01.347 --> 23:02.813
There had better not be.

23:02.849 --> 23:04.081
             I don't like your--

23:04.116 --> 23:05.148
Shoot, major.

23:05.184 --> 23:06.550
   Yeah!

23:06.586 --> 23:07.751
Shoot the works!

23:07.787 --> 23:09.152
    The works.

23:09.188 --> 23:11.488
       All right, I'm tired of
     sevens and elevens, anyway.

23:11.524 --> 23:13.457
ROGER:
Oh, don't say that!
Bite your tongue!

23:13.492 --> 23:14.491
           DEALER 2:
           Number...

23:15.861 --> 23:17.294
  ROGER:
Two sevens.

23:19.332 --> 23:20.830
He rolled
a fourteen.

23:22.601 --> 23:23.634
 Bring him out.

23:24.970 --> 23:26.570
          Oh, w-- Now,
   wait a minute. Now, wait.

23:26.605 --> 23:28.438
           Wait a minute.
            Hi, Jeannie.

23:28.474 --> 23:30.140
               Jeannie!
              Now, wait!

23:31.810 --> 23:33.677
[MOUTHS SILENTLY]

23:40.186 --> 23:46.290
             [♪♪♪]

23:46.325 --> 23:48.892
    And if you're interested
          in miracles,

23:48.927 --> 23:50.827
         it's a miracle
      we weren't arrested.

23:50.862 --> 23:52.962
    Now, Jeannie, I ask you
       not to go to Reno.

23:52.998 --> 23:55.432
      Oh. I've never been
   so embarrassed in my life.

23:55.467 --> 23:56.866
I was only
trying to help--

23:56.902 --> 23:58.134
            Help me.
     Yeah, I know. I know.

23:58.170 --> 23:59.903
       That's when I get
    into most of my trouble,

23:59.938 --> 24:01.371
       when you're trying
         to be helpful.

24:01.407 --> 24:02.839
           What was
     your excuse, major?

24:02.874 --> 24:04.408
                 I'm greedy.

24:04.443 --> 24:06.876
   Well, I-- I hope you both
  learned a lesson from this.

24:06.912 --> 24:08.745
            Well, I certainly
        learned my lesson, Tony.

24:08.780 --> 24:10.046
Oh, so have I,
master.

24:10.082 --> 24:12.048
I will not try to help
with the dice again.

24:12.084 --> 24:14.318
I am much better
with horseraces.

24:15.421 --> 24:17.153
             Horseraces? Really?

24:17.189 --> 24:18.355
   Oh, yes.

24:18.390 --> 24:19.556
I can make
any horse win.

24:19.592 --> 24:21.057
          Well, the track opened
                yesterday.

24:21.093 --> 24:22.526
             The three of us
             could have a ball--

24:22.561 --> 24:24.828
    That's a wonderful idea.
  You really like horseraces?

24:24.863 --> 24:26.029
                     Oh, do I?

24:26.064 --> 24:27.964
        You positive?
                        Oh,
                   you bet I am.

24:27.999 --> 24:29.733
     Well, how about that?
           Jeannie?

24:31.070 --> 24:33.236
        [CROWD CHEERING]

24:47.853 --> 24:52.356
             [♪♪♪]
